tion " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 318 47 "The governing equation solved i
s of the form :\n" }{TEXT 272 38 "theta(x)*dC/dt = -d(Fdiff+Fadv)/dx +
 R" }{TEXT 318 2 ",\n" }{TEXT 318 7 "where \n" }{TEXT 318 69 "- dX/dp \+
is the partial derivative of X with respect to p [M/L^3/[p]]\n" }{TEXT
 318 84 "- theta(x) = A(x)*por(x) for dissolved, and A(x)*(1-por(x)) f
or solid species [L^2]\n" }{TEXT 318 43 "- Fdiff = -(D(x)*theta(x)*dC/
dx) [M/L^2/T]\n" }{TEXT 318 34 "- Fadv  = (v*theta(x)*C)[M/L^2/T]\n" }
{TEXT 318 57 "- A is the cross section area [L^2], por is porosity [-]
\n" }{TEXT 318 49 "- v is the advection velocity [L/T], the sum of \n"
 }{TEXT 318 85 "the water flow velocity (vwat = water flow q in [L^3/T
]/theta(x), solutes only) and \n" }{TEXT 318 105 "an advective velocit
y w acting upon both solids and solutes (e.g. movement due to fixed re
ference frame)\n" }{TEXT 318 64 "- D is the effective diffusion coeffi
cient [L^2/T], the sum of \n" }{TEXT 318 59 "the molecular diffusion c
oefficient (Dmol, solutes only), \n" }{TEXT 318 39 "the bioturbation c
oefficient (Db) and \n" }{TEXT 318 73 "the dispersion coefficient (Dis
p = aL*|vwat|, solutes only, aL in [L]). \n" }{TEXT 318 101 "- R is th
e sum of the reaction terms [M/L^3/T] as specified in the reaction net
work established below" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 "" {TEXT 319 9 " Cavea
ts " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 318 60 "- for real numbers you should add
 a point after the number.\n" }{TEXT 318 30 "- make sure all units mat
ch. \n" }{TEXT 318 68 "e.g. rates and dXdt, or flux boundary condition
s and concentrations\n" }{TEXT 318 46 "for the conversion of solid to \+
solute units, \n" }{TEXT 318 76 "one may define temporary variables th
at can be used in the rate laws below:\n" }{TEXT 318 49 "s_dens := 2.5
; # solid density in [g/cm_solid^3]\n" }{TEXT 318 48 "sd := 1000. * s_
dens * (1. - por(j)) / por(j); \n" }{TEXT 318 66 "the factor 1.d03 con
verts cm^3 to liter, e.g. [g/cm^3] to [g/l]. \n" }{TEXT 318 40 "note t
hat you need to refer to porosity " }{TEXT 273 7 "exactly" }{TEXT 318 
11 " as por(j)." }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT 320 21 " Physics - \+
Parameters" }}{PARA 206 "" 0 "" {TEXT 321 19 "The list of length " }
{TEXT 26 20 "nparphys & nparphys2" }{TEXT 321 13 " is given by " }
{TEXT 26 22 "phys_name & phys_name2" }{TEXT 321 26 "; the values colle
cted in " }{TEXT 26 21 "phys_val & phys_val2." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 
"" {TEXT 319 33 " Spatial and temporal domain size" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 26 9 "tot_time:" }{TEXT 318 43 " total length of simulation (T, \+
e.g. years)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 26 10 "depth_max:" }{TEXT 318 60 
" spatial extent, e.g. total depth of simulation (L, e.g. cm)" }}
