 {TEXT 319 23 " Transport coefficients" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT
 26 3 "vaL" }{TEXT 318 95 ": longitudinal dispersivity (L). The disper
sion coefficient is calculated as Disp = aL*|vwat| \n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vi
q" }{TEXT 318 82 ": depth dependency of flow. 0: constant, else changi
ng with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vq0" }{TEXT 318 53 ": wa
ter flow (either constant or else at x=0, L^3/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "viw" 
}{TEXT 318 79 ": depth dependency of w. 0: constant, else changing wit
h depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vw0" }{TEXT 318 89 ": advectio
n velocity working on solids and solutes (either constant or else at x
=0, L/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 4 "viDb" }{TEXT 318 80 ": depth dependency of Db
. 0: constant, else changing with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 
4 "vDb0" }{TEXT 318 97 ": bioturbation coefficient working on solids a
nd solutes (either constant or else at x=0, L^2/T)\n" }{TEXT 318 1 "\n
" }{TEXT 318 134 "- user specified profiles of q(x), w(x) or Db(x) mus
t be defined in the fortran subroutines advcoeff.f and diffcoeff.f, re
spectively.\n" }{TEXT 318 87 "- the molecular diffusion coefficients f
or the species used are specified further below" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> 
